The CO hydrogenation was also carried out in the same reactor by feeding CO/H2/Ar with a molar ratio of 32/64/4 under the conditions of P = 2.0 MPa, T = 360 °C, and GHSV = 1000 mL g−1 h−1. The method for analyzing reactants and products was the same as that for the CO2 hydrogenation. The conversion rate of CO and the selectivity of CO2, methane, C2-4 HCs, C5+ HCs, MeOH, DME, and C2+ Oxys were calculated with the following equations.8ConversionrateofCO=[Fin(CO)−Fout(CO)]/Vm/mGaN\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
